# Requirements Document

## Introduction

This feature will transform the existing NGO website into a comprehensive content management platform that allows administrators to dynamically manage projects, blog posts, testimonials, announcements, and reports through a Filament admin panel. The system will provide public access to view projects and their details, read blog posts, view testimonials, access announcements, and download publicly available reports, while giving administrators full control over all content through an intuitive admin interface.

## Requirements

### Requirement 1: Dynamic Project Management

**User Story:** As an NGO administrator, I want to create, edit, and manage projects with detailed information, so that I can showcase our organization's work and impact to visitors.

#### Acceptance Criteria

1. WHEN an administrator accesses the admin panel THEN the system SHALL provide a projects management interface
2. WHEN creating a new project THEN the system SHALL require title, description, status, start date, and featured image
3. WHEN creating a project THEN the system SHALL allow optional fields for end date, budget, location, beneficiaries count, and gallery images
4. WHEN saving a project THEN the system SHALL validate all required fields and image formats
5. WHEN a project is published THEN the system SHALL make it visible on the public projects page
6. WHEN a visitor views the projects page THEN the system SHALL display all published projects with pagination
7. WHEN a visitor clicks on a project THEN the system SHALL show the detailed project page with all information and images

### Requirement 2: Blog Content Management

**User Story:** As an NGO administrator, I want to create and manage blog posts with rich content, so that I can share stories, updates, and insights with our audience.

#### Acceptance Criteria

1. WHEN an administrator creates a blog post THEN the system SHALL provide a rich text editor for content creation
2. WHEN creating a blog post THEN the system SHALL require title, content, author, and featured image
3. WHEN creating a blog post THEN the system SHALL allow optional fields for excerpt, tags, and publication date
4. WHEN saving a blog post THEN the system SHALL validate required fields and save as draft or published
5. WHEN a blog post is published THEN the system SHALL make it visible on the public blog page
6. WHEN visitors view the blog page THEN the system SHALL display published posts with pagination and search functionality
7. WHEN a visitor clicks on a blog post THEN the system SHALL show the full article with author information and publication date

### Requirement 3: Testimonials Management

**User Story:** As an NGO administrator, I want to collect and display testimonials from beneficiaries and partners, so that I can build trust and showcase our impact.

#### Acceptance Criteria

1. WHEN an administrator manages testimonials THEN the system SHALL provide an interface to add, edit, and delete testimonials
2. WHEN creating a testimonial THEN the system SHALL require name, content, and role/organization
3. WHEN creating a testimonial THEN the system SHALL allow optional fields for photo, location, and rating
4. WHEN saving a testimonial THEN the system SHALL validate required fields and allow approval status setting
5. WHEN testimonials are approved THEN the system SHALL display them on relevant public pages
6. WHEN visitors view pages with testimonials THEN the system SHALL show approved testimonials in an attractive format
7. WHEN displaying testimonials THEN the system SHALL rotate or paginate them if there are many

### Requirement 4: Announcements System

**User Story:** As an NGO administrator, I want to create and manage announcements, so that I can communicate important updates and news to website visitors.

#### Acceptance Criteria

1. WHEN an administrator creates an announcement THEN the system SHALL require title, content, and priority level
2. WHEN creating an announcement THEN the system SHALL allow setting publication and expiration dates
3. WHEN an announcement is active THEN the system SHALL display it prominently on the homepage
4. WHEN multiple announcements are active THEN the system SHALL display them based on priority and date
5. WHEN an announcement expires THEN the system SHALL automatically hide it from public view
6. WHEN visitors view the site THEN the system SHALL show current announcements in a noticeable but non-intrusive way
7. WHEN managing announcements THEN the system SHALL allow administrators to preview before publishing

### Requirement 5: Reports Management and Public Access

**User Story:** As an NGO administrator, I want to upload and manage reports, so that I can provide transparency and allow stakeholders to access important documents.

#### Acceptance Criteria

1. WHEN an administrator uploads a report THEN the system SHALL require title, description, file upload, and category
2. WHEN uploading a report THEN the system SHALL validate file types (PDF, DOC, DOCX) and size limits
3. WHEN saving a report THEN the system SHALL allow setting public/private visibility and publication date
4. WHEN a report is set to public THEN the system SHALL make it available for download on the reports page
5. WHEN visitors access the reports page THEN the system SHALL display all public reports with filtering by category and year
6. WHEN a visitor clicks download THEN the system SHALL serve the file securely and track download counts
7. WHEN managing reports THEN the system SHALL show download statistics to administrators

### Requirement 6: Filament Admin Panel Integration

**User Story:** As an NGO administrator, I want a unified admin interface to manage all content, so that I can efficiently maintain the website without technical knowledge.

#### Acceptance Criteria

1. WHEN an administrator logs into the admin panel THEN the system SHALL provide access to all content management features
2. WHEN navigating the admin panel THEN the system SHALL organize features into logical sections (Projects, Blog, Testimonials, Announcements, Reports)
3. WHEN using any admin feature THEN the system SHALL provide intuitive forms with proper validation and error messages
4. WHEN managing content THEN the system SHALL support bulk actions for common operations
5. WHEN viewing content lists THEN the system SHALL provide search, filtering, and sorting capabilities
6. WHEN editing content THEN the system SHALL auto-save drafts and prevent data loss
7. WHEN managing files THEN the system SHALL provide a media library with organization capabilities

### Requirement 7: Public Website Integration

**User Story:** As a website visitor, I want to easily navigate and access all NGO content, so that I can learn about the organization and its work.

#### Acceptance Criteria

1. WHEN visiting the website THEN the system SHALL provide clear navigation to all content sections
2. WHEN browsing content THEN the system SHALL maintain consistent design and user experience
3. WHEN viewing content on mobile devices THEN the system SHALL provide responsive design
4. WHEN searching for content THEN the system SHALL provide search functionality across projects and blog posts
5. WHEN loading pages THEN the system SHALL optimize performance with proper caching
6. WHEN accessing the site THEN the system SHALL ensure all public content is SEO optimized
7. WHEN interacting with the site THEN the system SHALL provide accessibility features for all users

### Requirement 8: Page Layout and Design System

**User Story:** As a website visitor, I want a visually appealing and consistent layout across all pages, so that I can easily navigate and engage with the NGO's content.

#### Acceptance Criteria

1. WHEN viewing any page THEN the system SHALL display a consistent navigation bar with logo on the left, menu in the middle, and donate button on the right
2. WHEN visiting the homepage THEN the system SHALL display a hero section with overlapping images, compelling heading, short paragraph, donate button, and about us button
3. WHEN viewing the homepage THEN the system SHALL show a "Who We Are" section with image, descriptive text, and read more button
4. WHEN browsing projects on homepage THEN the system SHALL display a carousel of project cards with image, title, short description, and read more button
5. WHEN viewing the homepage THEN the system SHALL show a partners section with organization logos in a carousel format, each linking to partner websites
6. WHEN viewing the homepage THEN the system SHALL display latest blog posts section with preview cards
7. WHEN scrolling through homepage THEN the system SHALL include a call-to-action (CTA) section encouraging visitor engagement

### Requirement 9: Partners Management System

**User Story:** As an NGO administrator, I want to manage partner organizations and their logos, so that I can showcase our collaborations and provide proper attribution.

#### Acceptance Criteria

1. WHEN an administrator manages partners THEN the system SHALL provide an interface to add, edit, and delete partner organizations
2. WHEN creating a partner THEN the system SHALL require organization name, logo upload, and website URL
3. WHEN creating a partner THEN the system SHALL allow optional fields for description, partnership type, and display order
4. WHEN saving a partner THEN the system SHALL validate logo format and website URL format
5. WHEN partners are active THEN the system SHALL display them in the homepage carousel
6. WHEN visitors click partner logos THEN the system SHALL open partner websites in new tabs
7. WHEN managing partners THEN the system SHALL allow administrators to reorder partners for display priority